The Bank of England takes note of concerns by offering 10 billion pounds in five weeks.
The Bank of England on Thursday was concerned about easing the current return of concerns over credit conditions, and announced an offer of ten billion pounds at the 5.75 per cent base rate in five weeks, an offer of unusual length.
'To alleviate concerns that financial market conditions will be particularly tight at the end of the year, and to give banks greater certainty in how they will organise their liquidity positions over this period, the Bank intends to offer a significant proportion of its planned reserve contribution during the maintenance period starting on 6 December in the form of a five-week open market operation,' it said in a statement.
