The Nuaria Group was in charge of developing what would be the largest residential complex in the Murcia municipality of Totana, which would involve the construction of more than 5,000 homes, a golf course and two hotels with "spa".
The company acquired 2,2 million square meters of land in Totana that was reclassified and its project would double the population of the municipality, which has 25,000 inhabitants.
