The prosecutor of the Balkans
Carla del Ponte has been relentlessly pursuing Balkan war criminals for eight years from the prosecutor's office of the Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia, based in The Hague.
Her term ends at the end of the year and Carla will leave with a bitter-sweet taste, because the main perpetrators of the Srebrenica massacre - in which 8,000 Bosnian Muslims were killed - former General Ratko Mladic and former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic, remain at large.
Their names are on that list from which the title of the documentary by Swiss filmmaker Marcel Schüpbach, 'La lista de Carla' (2006, not released in Spain) is taken, which, with the rhythm of a police thriller, follows the work of the Swiss prosecutor from Belgrade to New York to pursue the fugitive criminals and pressure the governments involved to tighten the siege.
What insurance is good for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver against possible accidents, is a major expense that depends on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Having the car is just the beginning.
And it is that choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of vehicle.
First of all, we have to be clear about what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is embodied in an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed premium in return for being liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is set taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, civil status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of the vehicle, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely you are to have an accident, the higher the premium.
This is why both men and women over 25 have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower accident rate because of their prudence.
Also, using counting, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency and, with it, the likelihood of some kind of accident.
The more frequent the odds.
There are many variables that insurance companies take into account when setting the premium price.
This is why the driver must study the situation carefully to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will explain here the most important factors in choosing one type of insurance, so that it is not only adapted to the characteristics of the insured but also offers a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 face several disadvantages when purchasing insurance at an affordable price, such as low driving experience and the age of the licence.
Although all-risk insurance is the ideal way to be well insured, other cheaper options exist.
The more cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk, all-expense policy, so that they get the coverage of an all-risk insurance policy at a more affordable price.
This type of arrangement would involve the customer paying a part of the amount of the loss.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the client contributes will be pre-established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount", says Luis Noguera, chief executive of First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third party insurance, so that the customer is insured against damage caused to third parties, but not against damage caused to his own car.
In addition, you would be covered for theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus and may reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the basic rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on the basic tariff.
"Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonuses", Noguera explains.
After the age of 25, it is easier for drivers to take out insurance, since accidents are reduced by accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to hire a franchise with a risk.
"Young people are not usually able to use their previous experience in handling accidents, even driving", says the European company's manager in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, after the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the customer is married but has no children yet, it is preferable to negotiate an all-risk insurance, provided that his financial situation allows it, of course.
On the other hand, children are considered by insurers to be the public with the lowest rate of injury, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk one with deductible (which may be EUR 300), or, where a high level of bonus is available, an extended third party insurance from the third year of the vehicle's life.
"They drive more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchising", sentences Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out an all-risk insurance policy with deductible (€150), or an extended third party insurance policy if the bonus is high.
Car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver against possible accidents but also because it is a major expense.
