20,000 people attend the first concert of the Spice Girls' Vancouver tour
The Spice Girls have started in Vancouver, Canada, before some 20,000 spectators, their first tour since they disbanded in 2000.
'Posh Spice' (Victoria Beckham), 'Scary Spice' (Melanie Brown), 'Baby Spice' (Emma Bunton), 'Sporty Spice' (Melanie Chisholm) and 'Ginger Spice' (Geri Halliwell) declared shortly before their gig at Vancouver's GM Place Stadium that the group's reunion is "brilliant".
About 20,000 people sold out for the concert, which included a video that told the story of the band that made waves in the late 1990s.
The reunion and world tour coincide with the release of a new album that features their main hits as well as two new songs, 'Headlines' and 'Voodoo', which in Spain is published by EMI.
The five Spice Girls took the stage wearing bracelets given to them by the husband of 'Posh Spice', British footballer David Beckham.
The athlete was among the crowd that crowded GM Place, even though Victoria's nerves had forbidden him from doing so days earlier.
